children.subject: +1. I am in the exact same situation.

history.content: Did you take summer courses? This is my 4th full (fall/spring) semester at Cal, and I took summer courses one summer, and CalCentral says that I have attended 5 semesters. If I recall correctly though, summer courses at Cal shouldn't count towards the maximum number of semesters you may attend at Cal.

children.subject: OP here: I didn't take any summer courses, so not sure why it's showing up as 6 semesters.

history.content:
On CalCentral, under the terms information section, it says that I have attended 6 semesters when I have really only attended 4 (and am currently on my 5th). Furthermore, it lists my class standing as a senior when I am really only a junior (although I have enough units to count as a senior -- but I thought that CalCentral should display your actual standing in terms of years and not units). Is this discrepancy normal?

I'm not sure if this is related, but I've also been receiving emails that are directed to the senior class, such as commencement speaker polls, etc. I'm worried that I might be listed as a graduating senior when I actually may want to stay at Cal for the full 4 years.

If it matters, I'm in EECS -- is there a maximum unit limit that once I exceed, I must graduate? 

Edit: I did not take summer courses.
history.subject: CalCentral displays incorrect class standing information
